  "texts": [
    "Faculty would need to curate AIgenerated content rigorously, ensuring that it aligns with established educational goals and evidence-based practices.",
    "To develop critical thinking, students should be encouraged to analyze and critique AI-generated information, helping them understand both the strengths and limitations of AI as a learning tool.",
    "As part of the integration process, faculty training on GAI capabilities and ethical considerations is essential, empowering educators to guide students effectively.",
    "The curriculum should also address ethics, data privacy, bias and emerging trends in AI, such as AI in robotic surgery and telemedicine.",
    "Finally, incorporating periodic evaluations of generative AI-driven modules will allow institutions to assess educational impact, adapt to technological advances, and ensure alignment with competency-based outcomes in orthopedic education.Integrating generative AI technologies into current educational structures necessitates careful planning to ensure that they supplement and improve traditional teaching techniques rather than replacing them."
